PHP test
rules - 
1) you need to complete this test within a day (24 hours)
2) you should upload the test results to a free hosting of your choice 
3) you should submit the code and resources that you used (books or online) by the end of the test
4) the second part (reading a code with errors) would be sent to you a day later 
5) as a courtesy and although this is just a test, you will be paid for your time 1000 Philippine pesos, sent via papal after the test is done


Browser Poll
 Write a PHP5, MySQL, jQuery & Bootstrap (responsive framework) utilizing any of the PHP frameworks like:

CodeIgniter/Symfony(1or2)/CakePHP/Zend Framework(1or2)/Yii/Laravel

It should
1) ask people for their favorite web browser. 
2) gather the information from all customers
3) gather browser and browsing information from each customer 

Please set a hard limit of 8 hours maximum for this task.  

It should gather this information via the following form: 
1.Your name 
2.Your email address 
3.Favorite browser (Allows only these options: Chrome, Safari, Firefox, Internet Explorer, 
Opera) 
4.Reason

Browser information to be gathered:
1) web IP
2) browsing history (last page)

After confirming the fields have been appropriately filled out (using client-side javascript and 
backend validation), it should save the information so that it can provide statistics for all 
submissions. 

After submitting their forms, The visitor should immediately see the total vote results, but not browser history and ip. that would be only in the admin section of that pole.

Total votes for each of the web browsers, as a raw count, and as a percentage of all 
votes. Underneath, a list showing all of the responses. This is to be done as table with columns: 

Name, Email, Browser, Reason, Time Submitted. It is to be in a specific order too; 
grouped firstly by web browser, then ordered by time/date. 

a graphic display of the results will be very appreciated as well 

To prevent duplications, if an email address is already in the poll, it should replace the old saved 
response with the newly submitted one. 

Upload the test project to any free hosting sites and make them work to show the demo. Email the source files & db sql dump.

Please do not include attachment of the PHP framework library & jQuery plugins including bootstrap.
